Subject: Great North American Extreme Bus Race

Announcing the First Annual Great North American Extreme Bus Race

You are invited to participate in the First Annual Great North American Extreme Bus Race coming up May 26, 2007.  The race will be open to all air-cooled VW bus owners.  Sorry, Dave, Subaru's nor other water-cooled motors are elgible.  The race will begin on Saturday, May 26th in Key West, FL and will end whenever the busses arrive in Fairbanks, Alaska.   The grand prize will be a set of Hancook RA-08's, a set of 4 KYB gas adjustable shocks, a megasquirt FI kit, SVDA distributor, Hot Spark electronic ignition, and a new Pop-up tent.  

Rules:  exceeding the speed limit is allowed if you're able.  Engine must be a stock 1.6, 1.7, 1.8, or 2.0L air-cooled VW motor.  Crews will consist of 2-person teams.  Busses will be issued a GPS locating device before the race begins and will be tracked from race-central in Chattanooga.  Busses are allowed only 16 hours/day of continuous driving.  A mandatory 8-hour rest period is required per 24 hours. Teams can choose any route they choose but must have proper documentation to get into Canada.   

Register today be mailing a non-refundable check for $500 to:

Kevin H. Roberts
Great North American Extreme Bus Race Central Command
PO Box 91342
Chattanooga, TN  37412.

Of course all of the Type 2 listees will be expected to participate.  May the best bus win....KR

 
